{
  "stem": "945.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "My dad was a soldier in the First World War-- fought on the Italian front, used to talk about it sometime.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So their opinion was, it's not possible.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Something isn't right.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The reason I am mentioning that is because that was an underlying-- underlying [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] part of our tragedy.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Explain that, please.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The explanation is that nobody until the last moment believed that what was happening was really happening.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the Germans and the Nazis and all our enemies used that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They used that to further their ultimate goal, which was our destruction.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] While this was happening and events started to unfold themselves a little bit better, so that people started to question whether maybe they were wrong in thinking that what was happening in Germany was not happening.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] A lot of young Jewish people and even maybe some older Jewish people started to think that maybe they should hope for communism to solve or rescue us from-- from whatever the Nazis might bring.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In 1939, the Soviet Union and Germany divided Poland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Living in Vishnitz, which was on the Polish border on the other side of the river-- the river was the Cheremosh.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "On the other side of the River Cheremosh was a little shtetl called Kitev-- Kuty.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Kuty also had a Jewish population.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I know, because my grandfather's sister lived in Kuty.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we were once over on the other side to visit her.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] In '39, when Poland was divided, instead of Poland being our neighbor or our border across the river, it became the Soviet Union.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
